{"serial": "22031", "department_serial": 21, "code": "PH2030", "class": "A", "name": {"en": "Experimental Physics and Method II", "ch": "實驗物理與方法II"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Lin, I"], "ch": ["伊林"]}, "credits": 6, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 3, "session": ["5", "6", "7", "8", "9", "A", "B"]}, "loc": {"building": "S4", "room": "204"}}], "isRequired": true, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "物理學系", "en": "Department of Physics"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "全部使用", "en": "All"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 14, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "實驗物理與方法課程為物理系學生學習實驗物理的相連貫的二基礎入門課程，共為期兩年。每周以約二至三小時課堂講授、發表、與討論為主，其餘時間於在實驗室進行實驗，課後進行文獻調查、數據分析與報告撰寫。以培養學生從事基礎實驗物理動手能力，與研究所需基本態度與方法學訓練為基礎理念。將透過此二連貫課程，對學生進行實驗探索方法學的基礎訓練：如自我與團隊自主學習、系統思維與辯證、電子、機械、電腦、英文等實驗工具操控、口頭與書面論述、議題設定、研究計畫執行團隊合作等方法學鍛鍊。\n第四學期的課程以專題計畫執行為主，第三學期寒假，學生須就第三學期選定之議題與初步進行的實驗，進行閱讀相關論文與書籍，與助教反覆討論，進行下學期自行設計實驗的準備，並於第四學期完成實驗專題，且於期末物理小年會進行壁報發表。學期間每週並由一組學生就其專題研究議題所涉文獻與書籍所呈現的原理、實驗方法、成果，以四十分鐘進行統整口頭報告，並以剩餘時間對上述報告及專題計畫所與問題進行口頭討論，下次上課前每一學生除須繳交上週實驗的書面報告與未來一周實驗計畫的書面報告外，並須撰寫半頁總結報告，期望學生對當代實驗的議題、原理、技術有深度瞭解，以利其所進行的研究議題之承先啟後，順利開展。", "en": "The “Experimental physics and method” is a series of two-year course for the entry level physics major students. Its goal is to train the basic altitude, the methodology, and the basic technical background of conducting experimental physics research. It focuses on self- and group independent studies, systematic thinking and dialectics, project setting and execution, oral and written presentations, team works and management, and manipulating tools such as electronics, computer, machine shop skills, English and mathematics, etc.."}, "outline": {"ch": "第四學期的課程以專題計畫執行為主，第三學期寒假，學生須就第三學期選定之議題與初步進行的實驗，進行閱讀相關論文與書籍，與助教反覆討論，進行下學期自行設計實驗的準備，並於第四學期完成實驗專題，且於期末物理小年會進行壁報發表。學期間每週並由一組學生就其專題研究議題所涉文獻與書籍所呈現的原理、實驗方法、成果，以四十分鐘進行統整口頭報告，並以剩餘時間對上述報告及專題計畫所與問題進行口頭討論，下次上課前每一學生除須繳交上週實驗的書面報告與未來一周實驗計畫的書面報告外，並須撰寫半頁總結報告，期望學生對當代實驗的議題、原理、技術有深度瞭解，以利其所進行的研究議題之承先啟後，順利開展。", "en": "The fourth semester course is focused on the experimental project execution. In the second half of the third semester, each team has to do literature search on a new physics topic published in the past five years on the prestige journals such as Nature, Science, Physical Review Letters, etc, determine their topics, and complete the preliminary experimental test. In the winter break, each team has to more deeply complete their literature search and background reading, and prepare their experimental hard and soft wares. In the fourth semester, each team has to complete their project and give a poster presentation in the annual physics meeting of our physics department. Each team also has to give a 40 min. oral presentation of reviewing the background for their research project in the fourth semester. The rest time in each class will be left for discussing their presentation, and the new finding and difficulties in executing their experimental project last week."}, "textbook": {"ch": "與研究相關各式物理重要期刊、書籍、與網路資訊", "en": "Project related information from physics journals, books, and internet information"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100%", "en": "100%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "研討\n實習/實驗\n個別指導", "en": ["Seminar", "Practical Training Lab", "Individual Instruction"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "實驗背景40分鐘口頭報告 10％\n每週書面報告  25％\n課堂討論表現 15％\n專題實驗執行 50％", "en": "40 min. oral presentation of research project related background search 10％\nWeekly written report 25％\nClass discussion performance 15％ \nResearch project performance 50％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "週一 1700 to 1800", "en": "Monday 1700 to 1800"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "視該班專題實驗計畫完成度而定。", "en": "Depending on the completeness degree of students' \nproject execution"}, "domain": {"ch": "共同物理課程", "en": "共同物理課程"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "基礎物理", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "專題研